  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It is generally assumed that renal blood flow is symmetric in the absence of renal artery
      stenosis. The importance of studying the function of both kidneys separately is because it
      cannot be assumed that they are functionally equal.The aim of the present study is to
      evaluate whether this is really in patients with essential hypertension and/or moderate
      kidneys loss.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      To validate color Doppler ultrasonography of renal arteries for the assessment of renal blood
      flow (RBF), we comparing left and right RBF estimates and their sum (total RBF) by
      echo-Doppler with data obtained by 99mTc-DTPA scintigraphy in 50 patients with hypertension
      and/or moderate renal failure, compared with 30 normal control subjects.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
